    description:
      "<p><b>Raising the standards in safety &ndash; join us and make a difference.</b></p><p>We are Cobalt Safety and are passionate about raising the standard in safety and protecting both the workers and the companies they work for. Founded by a former Ministry of Labour Inspectors, Cobalt Safety is rapidly becoming recognized as a the visionary leader that is advancing and innovating safety across all stakeholders.</p><p>Are you passionate about making a difference in health and safety? Ready to start a hands-on role where you can showcase your expertise, ability to learn and willingness to lead?? At Cobalt Safety, we're a dynamic team of safety professionals dedicated to unparalleled safety training and oversight delivered with the most exceptional service to our clients.</p><p>We are a rapidly growing international company and are proud to offer team members with unlimited opportunities for professional growth and advancement. This is a collaborative environment that welcomes new ideas and perspectives from across varied professional experiences and backgrounds. If this sounds like you, and you are an individual that is eager to contribute early, please get in touch by July 15th, 2024</p><p><b>Why Join Us?</b></p><ul><li><b>Team Spirit</b>: Imagine being a part of a team that supports each other, provides training and learning opportunities and challenges you to be the best in the industry; that is the team at Cobalt Safety.</li><li><b>Exciting Challenges</b>: Take on diverse projects that enhance your skills and expertise. We work on projects from construction to entertainment events and live concerts. Our opportunities for various industry experiences are wide.</li><li><b>Exceptional Learning</b>: Led by former Ministry of Labour Investigators and trainers, we provide extensive training and insights into health and safety through our Masterclass training and team experience.</li><li><b>Career Growth</b>: Potential for exciting opportunities in various industries. Lot's to see and learn.</li><li><b>Impactful Work</b>: Make a real difference in workplace safety and compliance.</li></ul><p><b>Key Responsibilities</b></p><ul><li><b>Safety Programs</b>: Coordinate and manage client on-site safety programs.</li><li><b>Inspections &amp; Reporting</b>: Conduct workplace compliance inspections, report writing, and follow-up.</li><li><b>Incident Management</b>: Execute workplace safety management and minor accident investigations. Opportunities for major accident investigations for the right candidate.</li><li><b>Training &amp; Verification</b>: Lead contractor site orientations and documentation verifications. Opportunities to become a safety trainer.</li><li><b>Audits &amp; Coverage</b>: Perform health and safety audits and provide emergency coverage</li></ul><p><b>What We&rsquo;re Looking For</b></p><ul><li><b>Experience</b>: 3- 5 years in safety, construction, and project site safety.</li><li><b>Rail Experience</b>: Not mandatory but helpful.</li><li><b>Skills</b>: Strong communication, leadership, and organizational skills.</li><li><b>Knowledge</b>: Solid understanding of the Occupational Health and Safety Act.</li><li><b>Tech Savvy</b>: Proficient in Microsoft Word, Excel, and Outlook.</li><li><b>Qualifications</b>: Valid Driver's License, NCSO, CRSP certificates are a plus.</li><li><b>Location: GTA &amp; Halton &amp; Hamilton Region</b></li></ul><p><b>Perks</b></p><ul><li><b>Competitive Wages</b>: $28.00 - $38.00 per hour depending on experience.</li><li><b>Comprehensive Benefits</b>: Including dental and extended health care.</li><li><b>Work-Life Balance</b>: Monday to Friday, 8-hour shifts with potential overtime pay.</li><li><b>Potential for Travel</b>: As we grow, so does our geographic footprint and there are opportunities to travel for the right candidate</li></ul><p><b>Apply Now!</b></p><p>Send your resume and cover letter to careers@cobaltsafety.ca. Deadline: July 16th, 2024. We thank all interested applicants and your resume will be kept on file but only shortlisted candidates will be contacted for interviews.</p><p>Job Type: Full-time</p><p>Pay: $28.00-$38.00 per hour</p><p>Expected hours: 35 &ndash; 45 per week</p><p>Benefits:</p><ul><li>Company events</li><li>Dental care</li><li>Disability insurance</li><li>Extended health care</li><li>Paid time off</li><li>Tuition reimbursement</li><li>Vision care</li></ul><p>Schedule:</p><ul><li>Monday to Friday</li><li>Weekends as needed</li></ul><p>Supplemental pay types:</p><ul><li>Overtime pay</li></ul><p>Ability to commute/relocate:</p><ul><li>Greater Toronto Area, ON: reliably commute or plan to relocate before starting work (required)</li></ul><p>Experience:</p><ul><li>Safety: 3 years (required)</li></ul><p>Work Location: In person</p><p>Application deadline: 2024-06-30<br/>Expected start date: 2024-07-08</p>",
